      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p> Former governor of New York and major-general in the War of 1812. </p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p> Collection consists of letters by Morgan Lewis to his wife, Mrs. Getrude (Livingston)
            Lewis. The letters related to Lewis' military service under General Henry Dearborn at
            his headquarters in Albany, New York, in 1812, and on the Niagra frontier, and at
            Sackets Harbor, New York, in 1813; and under General James Wilkinson at Sackets Harbor
            and in the campaign against Montreal in 1813. </p>
      </scopecontent>
